      "side": 1,
      "message": "Hello\nThis is both a GHA minion setup issue and a pre-commit config issue.\nfor pre-commit issues cf other comments\n\nfor minion issue cf below\n\nI can read in the related logs\n\nRun actions/setup-python@a309ff8b426b58ec0e2a45f0f869d46889d02405\n  with:\n    python-version: 3.11\n[...]\nModuleNotFoundError: No module named \u0027lib2to3\u0027\n\n\nSo lib2to3 module is invoked by autopep8 on python v3.11\nAccording to comments in the related autopep8 tracker https://github.com/hhatto/autopep8/issues/581\n\"PendingDeprecationWarning: lib2to3 package is deprecated and may not be able to parse Python 3.10+\"\nand the lib2to3 dependency was removed from autopep8 v2.1.0\n\nIf you can\u0027t force a version above on the precommit config file,\nyou may ask the minion admin to use either:\n- a previous version of python\nor preferably\n- a more recent one to have a dependency resolution that allows pre-commit to use a more recent versions of autopep8\n\nhope this helps",
      "parentUuid": "e51a8d18_ffc2d6b7",
